The paper discusses the development of a predictive approach for cyber defense to strengthen cloud infrastructures specifically utilized by critical infrastructures. This involves the use of techniques such as Game Theory, Machine Learning, and Bayesian Networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of Markov Decision Process (MDP), which is commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, and cs.SE.
